      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "מְזַמְרות",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", occurring five times, and always translated \"snuffers.\" A slightly different form of the word is translated \"pruning-hooks \"four times in the Prophets Isaiah, Joel, Micah. No doubt these ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "snuffers",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " were something different from the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "tongs",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of the preceding verse; the use of one may have been rather to cut the wicks, and the other to trim them. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The spoons;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "כַפ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This is the word used so often for the \"hand,\" but the essential idea of which is the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "hollow",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of either hand or foot or other thing, and among other things of a spoon shape. The word is used of the frankincense-cups (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 7:14, 20, 26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") brought to the dedication of the tabernacle by the several princes. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The censers;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "מַחְתּות",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". These were \"snuff-dishes\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 25:38",
        "children": []
      },
      {
